Vice President Kamala Harris addressed a gathering at the Renaissance Hotel in Washington, D.C., expressing condolences for the mass shooting that occurred in Uvalde, Texas earlier that day. She called for action to prevent such tragedies from happening again and emphasized the need for reasonable and sensible public policies. Harris also spoke about the importance of Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) representation in decision-making rooms and the responsibility to advocate for those who are not present. She highlighted the progress made in addressing hate crimes and increasing AAPI representation in the government. Harris concluded by urging everyone to remain focused on creating a better future for all people and to envision what can be, unburdened by the past.